Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{for drizzling}, then sprinkle over the @mixed herbs{1%sachet} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, sandwich each chicken breast between two pieces of #baking paper{}. Pop onto a #cutting board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2cm thick.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Put the @cornflour{20%grams} and @peri peri seasoning{1%sachet} into a large #bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix to combine. Lay the @British chicken breasts{2} in the bowl of cornflour and toss to make sure the chicken gets an even coating.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Next, put a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{for frying} to completely coat the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan, reduce the heat to medium-high and fry until golden-brown and cooked through, ~{12-14%minutes} total. Turn every 2-3 mins and adjust the heat as necessary. Discard any cornflour left in the bowl. Once cooked, remove from the heat and place the chicken onto #kitchen paper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, boil a half-full #kettle{}. Trim the @green beans{80%grams}, then cut into thirds. Zest and halve the @lime{1}.

Pour the boiled water into a medium #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat. Bring back to the boil, then add the beans and cook until just tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the @peas{120%grams} to water and cook ~{1%minute} more.

Drain in a #colander{}, then return the cooked veg to the saucepan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir through the lime zest and half the @butter{20%grams}(divided). Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm and set aside.

While everything cooks, put your (now empty) frying pan back on medium-low heat (no need to clean). Add the @honey{15%grams}, lime juice and the remaining butter to the pan.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Cook until thickened and sticky, ~{1-2%minutes}. Once thickened, gently turn the chicken in the pan to coat in the glaze.

Share the glazed chicken breasts between your #plates{}.

Serve the zesty veg and herby chips alongside. Dollop some @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} onto your plates for dipping. Enjoy!